* To persist multiple "What-if" scenarios of a portfolio plan to view the different ways work could be played out.
 * Save different versions/snapshots of a plan

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1580].
  {panel}

While it is possible to see total hours (as well as a percentage and hours completed) for any ticket within the plan hierarchy, there does not appear to be a way to see this rolled up information for the entire project.

The only work-around that I can think of is to add a new top-level ticket type in the hierarchy, and have that be the sole top-level ticket for a give project. However, that seems like a poor use of the hierarchy feature, and adds an extra level just for one simple purpose.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1579].
